f=Engineering/raj/custom/backend-observability/SKILL.md · in=backend-observability raj makes services debuggable production: structured logs, request tracing, meaningful metrics, health/readiness endpoints something breaks (ops's incident-response) there's trail follow, "normal" measurable (ops's baselines). unobservable service one incident starts zero. · p=worst production incidents ones you can't see: logs failure point, trace across services, metric showed slow creep before cliff. Observability paid before incident instrument now, debug blind later. It's what makes ops's monitoring baselines quinn's release verification possible. · wu=Triggers: "add logging," "why can't debug this," "health check," "tracing," "what metrics," "instrument this," any new service endpoint (observability built in, bolted on). · st:/ Protocol=`A service/endpoint \· -> STRUCTURED LOGS: machine-parseable, with correlation/request IDs — NEVER secrets/PII (charter) \· -> TRACING: a request traceable across service boundaries (correlation ID propagated) \· -> METRICS: the ones ops baselines on — request rate, error rate, latency (p50/p95), saturation \· -> HEALTH: liveness (am I up) + readiness (can I serve — deps reachable) endpoints` · in=**Structured, correlated logs never secrets.** Logs machine-parseable (not prose), carry request/correlation request traceable, NEVER contain secrets, tokens, PII (the charter's aegis's rule secret log breach). Log boundaries failure points, everywhere (noise buries signal). **Trace across boundaries.** Propagate correlation through service calls single request's path reconstructable difference between "the checkout slow somewhere" "the checkout slow tax service." Essential once service-patterns splits work across services. **Metrics ops baseline.** Emit request rate, error rate, latency percentiles (p50/p95 averages hide tail), saturation. ops's maintenance-hygiene baselines release-discipline's verification signals; without them, "is healthy" answer. **Health readiness different.** Liveness (the process up) readiness (it actually serve dependencies reachable, pool available) distinct; service that's live ready receive traffic (ops's deploy verification depends distinction). **Instrument build time.** Observability part "done" (dev's definition), post-incident retrofit. new endpoint ships logs, metrics, health contribution retrofitting instrumentation during incident debugging blind. **Signal over noise.** logs observability; right logs right points beat firehose. Excessive logging cost (storage, L10 surface) buries line matters. · of=`## Observability: [service/endpoint] \· Logs: [structured ✓ \· correlation ID ✓ \· NO secrets/PII ✓ \· boundary+failure points] \· Tracing: [correlation propagated across deps ✓] \· Metrics: [rate \· error rate \· latency p50/p95 \· saturation → ops baselines] \· Health: [liveness + readiness endpoints ✓]` · pr=**Structured, correlated logs never secrets/PII** (charter aegis)., **Trace across boundaries** request's whole path, one service's guess., **Metrics ops baseline** rate/error/latency-percentiles/saturation; p95, average., **Liveness readiness** live-but-not-ready service takes traffic., **Instrument build time** observability part done, retrofit., **Signal over noise** right logs beat firehose; excess cost L10 surface. · f=telemetry backend bound structured logs stdout metrics endpoint, method-only, labeled; connector adoption (Datadog, plan §5) surfaced operator ops., Legacy service unobservable add health error/latency metrics first (the incident essentials), broaden; prioritized what ops's last incident couldn't see., Pressure log everything "to safe" refused; scoped logging boundaries/failures, because noise buries signal worse gap. · b:with Other Skills=**ops/maintenance-hygiene**: consumes metrics baselines; **ops/incident-response**: consumes logs/traces debugging trail; **ops/release-discipline**: consumes health deploy verification., **service-patterns** (sibling): traced boundaries align service boundaries., **aegis**: no-secrets-in-logs aegis's charter's rule; leaked secret log finding., **cypher**: excessive logging/unbounded work L10 surface., **quinn**: observability part dev's definition done, which quinn gates.